# A hole-free embedded literal forwards to a component's Attrs bag (see
# embedded_attr_prop.txtar), but one carrying an @{ } interpolation is still
# rejected: forwarding a hole into a bag needs JS/CSS-context-correct per-hole
# escaping, a separate feature. The author moves it to an element inside.
-- input.gsx --
package views

component Card(title string) {
	<div>{title}</div>
}

component Page(id string) {
	<Card title="Hi" x-model=js`items[@{id}]`/>
}
-- diagnostics.golden --
8:19: embedded js attribute literal "x-model" with @{ } interpolation cannot be used as a component prop on <Card> yet; pass an ordinary prop value or move the literal to an element inside the component
